  "title": "Closed-loop, machine learning–driven optimization of reactor yields in reactive carbon electrolyzers",
  "experiments_summary": "The study employed a closed-loop automated platform (AdaCarbon) to optimize reactor yield in reactive carbon electrolyzers. Six experimental parameters were varied: bicarbonate temperature (25–80°C), concentration (0.5–3.05 M), flow rate (30–200 mL/min), KOH concentration (0.05–3 M), flow rate (6–30 mL/min), and total applied current density (50–350 mA/cm²). Silver nanoparticle catalysts were spray-coated onto gas-diffusion electrodes using an automated spray-coater. The automated test cell (ATC) performed 5-minute electrolysis runs with bipolar membranes separating cathode and anode compartments. Products were analyzed via in-line mass spectrometry. Bayesian optimization with Gaussian process regression and q-noisy expected improvement acquisition function guided experiment selection. The reactor yield campaign initialized with 12 random experiments, followed by 10 optimizer-guided runs, 5 researcher-defined space-filling points, and continued until convergence after 52 total experiments. A separate JCO optimization campaign initialized with all 52 reactor yield experiments and ran 5 additional iterations. SHAP analysis identified parameter importance. Validation experiments tested realistic capture conditions using mixed bicarbonate-carbonate electrolytes with fixed 3M K+ concentration and varying bicarbonate:carbonate ratios."
